		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Spintronics</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Spintronics</b> (a <a href="/wiki/Neologism" title="Neologism">neologism</a> meaning "spin transport electronics"<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>), also known as magnetoelectronics, is an <a href="/wiki/Emerging_technology" title="Emerging technology" class="mw-redirect">emerging technology</a> which exploits the intrinsic <a href="/wiki/Spin_(physics)" title="Spin (physics)">spin</a> of <a href="/wiki/Electron" title="Electron">electrons</a> and its associated <a href="/wiki/Magnetic_moment" title="Magnetic moment">magnetic moment</a>, in addition to its fundamental electronic charge, in <a href="/wiki/Solid_state_(electronics)" title="Solid state (electronics)">solid-state devices</a>.</p>
